&lt;h2&gt;Position Summary&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Effectual Program Managers are members of the Project Management Office within Effectual Professional Services (PS) organization. They are responsible for ensuring that Effectual’s customers receive exceptional service that leverages the full breadth of Effectual’s experience, expertise, and execution capabilities. Program Managers oversee all delivery activities for their assigned engagements across the full portfolio of offerings Effectual provides and are accountable for driving successful project outcomes on time and within budget. They develop strong working relationships with customers and collaborate with Account Executives, Solution Architects, and senior members of Effectual’s PS organization to deliver consistent, high-quality results. You are a “Brand Ambassador” and are expected to advocate for achieving our customer’s defined outcomes through the delivery of our services. Additionally, you will mentor other Project Managers within the organization and provide guidance and direction in developing Intellectual Capital to ensure a repeatable process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;A Glimpse into the Daily Routine of a Senior Program Manager&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Each day, a Program Manager navigates between high-level strategy and hands-on execution, ensuring complex programs align with business objectives. They engage regularly with executive stakeholders to provide updates, resolve challenges, and secure the resources needed to keep initiatives moving forward. Simultaneously, they oversee budgets, manage risk, and lead cross-functional teams through transformational change with clear communication and strong leadership. Their role is pivotal in turning strategic vision into measurable results while cultivating a culture of collaboration and accountability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Essential Duties and Responsibilities&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ensuring Customer Retention Through Exceptional Delivery Quality and Program Leadership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide strategic leadership and direction for complex and high-impact programs, ensuring alignment with organizational objectives and priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Champion Effectual&#39;s Delivery Framework through Scrum or hybrid practices, facilitating collaboration with project resources, partner teams, and customer stakeholders to monitor progress, remove obstacles, and drive accountability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinating staffing of customer workstreams and serve as the escalation point for risk management and mitigation of customer concerns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Furthering Effectual’s Relationship with Assigned Customers&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cultivating productive, trusted relationships with key customer executives and stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand customer business priorities and objectives, and ensure that Effectual&#39;s work is focused on delivering value, driving outcomes, and supporting strategic goals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Establishing and Maintaining Excellent Executive Level Relationships&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage executive stakeholders with regular program updates, addressing concerns and securing necessary support and resources&lt;strong&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate objectives and requirements into actionable project plans and deliverables.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate and negotiate timeline adjustments, prepare and deliver change orders, and conduct weekly status meetings and reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Research and respond to client inquiries, including technical and billing questions, in a timely manner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Foster long-term client partnerships, identifying opportunities for repeat business and referrals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
